  "prompt": "What is an alter ego really?",
  "response": "An alter ego is a distinct personality or persona that is different from a person's usual or primary self. Here are some key characteristics:\n\n1. Psychological definition\n- A secondary or alternative personality\n- Often represents hidden or suppressed aspects of oneself\n- Can be a conscious creation or unconscious manifestation\n\n2. Common contexts\n- Creative expression (artists creating performance personas)\n- Psychological coping mechanism\n- Professional or social role-playing\n- Superhero/fictional character concepts\n\n3. Characteristics\n- Usually shares some core traits with the original personality\n- Might have different behaviors, attitudes, or skills\n- Can be more confident, uninhibited, or powerful\n- Often represents an idealized or alternative version of oneself\n\n4. Examples\n- Musicians creating stage personas (David Bowie's Ziggy Stardust)\n- Actors adopting character personalities\n- Superheroes with secret identities (Clark Kent/Superman)\n- Professional personas different from personal self\n\n5. Psychological purpose\n- Exploration of different identity aspects\n- Emotional protection\n- Creative expression\n- Managing complex social interactions\n\nAn alter ego is essentially a \"second self\" that allows individuals to explore different facets of their personality in a structured, intentional way.",
